abstract: EVEN if a long and heavy rainfall relieves the current drought, a spokesman for Governor Byrne said last week, the long-range picture "is that we're going to have a big problem."
headline_main: Water Problem Called a Long-Range One; Water Crisis Called Long-Range Problem for State

abstract: IT was wild. The ultimate romantic-political retail spectacle. There, last night at Bloomingdale's Third Avenue entrance, under a banner emblazoned with "China, Heralding the Dawn of a New Era," stood  hundreds of men in serious black and women in high brocade and glimmering satins waiting to see the store's latest foray into grandiose, hands-across-the-sea, merchandise promotion.
headline_main: China Night on 3d Avenue; It Was China Night on Third Avenue
headline_print_headline: China Night on 3d Avenue; It Was China Night on Third Avenue
